sequenceDiagram
    participant Build as Image Build<br/>(Konflux)
    participant Init as Init Container<br/>(odh-pipelines-components)
    participant Vol as Shared Volume<br/>/config/managed-pipelines/
    participant KFP as KFP API Server<br/>(managed by DSPO)
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Train as Training Task Pod<br/>(Kubeflow Trainer)
    participant PVC as PVC<br/>(Shared Workspace)
    participant Eval as Evaluation Task<br/>(lm-eval / Eval Hub)
    participant MR as Model Registry<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant OGX as OGX API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Milvus as Milvus<br/>19530/TCP gRPC
    participant Docling as Text Extraction<br/>(Docling in AutoRAG)

    rect rgb(220, 240, 220)
        Note over Build,KFP: Flow 1: Managed Pipeline Initialization
        Build->>Init: Compile @dsl.pipeline → YAML<br/>(at build time)
        Init->>Init: Check RELATED_IMAGE_* env vars<br/>(recompile if present)
        Init->>Vol: Copy managed-pipelines.json +<br/>compiled YAML specs
        Vol->>KFP: Read pipeline manifests<br/>(emptyDir mount)
        KFP->>KFP: Register managed pipelines
    end

    rect rgb(220, 220, 245)
        Note over HF,MR: Flow 2: Fine-Tuning Pipeline (SFT/LoRA/OSFT)
        HF-->>PVC: Step 1: Download dataset<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, HF_TOKEN
        S3-->>PVC: Step 1 (alt): Download from S3<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
        PVC->>Train: Step 2: Read dataset from PVC
        Train->>Train: Step 3: Train model<br/>(via K8s API → ClusterTrainingRuntime)
        Train->>PVC: Step 4: Write model checkpoint
        PVC->>Eval: Step 5: Read model for evaluation
        Eval->>Eval: Run lm-eval benchmarks<br/>or submit to Eval Hub (HTTPS/443)
        Eval->>MR: Step 6: Register trained model<br/>HTTP/80, Plaintext, No Auth
    end

    rect rgb(245, 230, 220)
        Note over S3,Milvus: Flow 3: RAG Optimization Pipeline
        S3->>Docling: Step 1: Discover documents<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
        S3->>Docling: Step 2: Download & extract text<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
        Docling->>OGX: Step 3: Generate embeddings<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, API key
        OGX->>Milvus: Step 4: Store in vector DB<br/>HTTPS/443 via OGX, API key
        OGX->>OGX: Step 5: AI4RAG optimizer<br/>hyperparameter search
        OGX-->>OGX: Step 6: Output leaderboard<br/>HTML artifact
    end
